This is, in my opinion, one of the deepest questions in physics and information theory. It gets at what information is, independent of the thing carrying it.

The key insight is:

The carrier changes. The pattern persists.

Information is not the electron. It is not the photon. It is the relationship encoded in the state of the carrier.

For example:

Electron
    │
    ▼
Voltage difference
    │
    ▼
Laser
    │
    ▼
Photon pulse
    │
    ▼
Photodiode
    │
    ▼
Electron again

Nothing physical made the journey except energy and interactions.

What survived?

The pattern.

⸻

Think of music.

Composer
    ↓
Paper sheet music
    ↓
Piano vibrations
    ↓
Air pressure waves
    ↓
Ear
    ↓
Neural spikes
    ↓
Memory

Every substrate changed.

Ink.
Wood.
Air.
Hair cells.
Neurons.

Yet we’d all say it’s still the same song.

Why?

Because the relations were preserved.

⸻

This suggests a hierarchy.

Level 0

* Matter

Level 1

* State

Level 2

* Pattern

Level 3

* Meaning

Each level can survive replacement of the lower one.

Replace every neuron.

Replace every atom.

Replace paper with sound.

Replace sound with binary.

Replace binary with light.

As long as the transformations preserve the relevant relationships, the higher-level pattern remains.

⸻

